    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using lsp-completion, `autocompletedelay` is not being respected and the pop-up menu is appearing instantly. This bug is not seen when not using lsp-completion, ie. when `complete` doesn't include `o`.\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/10beb649-e25c-4402-9d80-dd94f3d21ff2\n\nAs you can see in the above video, ignoring the time that the LSP took to start, the completion menu appears instantly without respecting `autocompletedelay`. When `complete` is reset (ie. no longer using lsp-completion), `autocompletedelay` is respected, and the completion menu doesn't appear until 5000ms.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.o.autocomplete = true\nvim.opt.completeopt = { 'menu', 'menuone', 'noselect', 'popup' }\nvim.o.autocompletedelay = 5000\nvim.o.complete = 'o'\n\nvim.lsp.config['lua_ls'] = {\n  cmd = { 'lua-language-server' },\n  filetypes = { 'lua' },\n  settings = {\n    Lua = {\n      runtime = {\n        version = 'LuaJIT',\n      },\n    },\n  },\n}\nvim.lsp.enable('lua_ls')\n```\n\nLaunch Neovim with above config and type something, autocomplete menu will popup instantly if completion exists.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`autocompletedelay` should be respected. In above reproduction, it should have taken 5 seconds for the menu to display.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\ntested on v0.12.0-dev-2583+g1491e7b5bd and v0.13.0-dev-29+g1bcf2d7f90\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI tried having 'o' in `complete` in Vim, it didn't give any issues. And vim doesn't have lsp-completion.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot 1.26.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nBuild from repo",
